title: Maintenance6
---
VEX: Well, you’re currently composed of a set of mismatched parts. Each time I leave you alone for a significant period of time, I’ve got to make sure that everything is still working properly before I really get in the weeds with you.
VEX: Sort of like tuning an old guitar.
<<endDialogue end>>
===

title: Maintenance7
---
EL1-5e: Thank you for that explanation. But that is not what I meant.
EL1-5e: I meant why are you fixing me? You are not associated with ASCO, nor any major airline companies.
EL1-5e: So, if not for my original purpose, to what end am I being set to. . . ?
<<endDialogue end>>
